Must-Haves (Core Features & Essential Deliverables):
Must-Haves (Core Features & Essential Deliverables)
1. CSV File Ingestion – Ability to upload and process ShadowSight-generated CSV files,
including appending new data.
2. Interactive Data Visualisation – Various graph types (line charts, bar charts, heatmaps, etc.)
to display user activity trends.
3. Date Range Filtering & Selection – Users must be able to select specific time periods to
analyse trends.
4. Client-Side Data Processing – All operations should be performed in-memory without
backend servers or databases.
5. Shareable Web Link Access – Clients should be able to access the dashboard online without
authentication requirements.
6. Machine Learning Insights – Data-driven analysis to suggest granular mitigation strategies
based on detected activity patterns.
7. Smooth Animations & Transitions – Visual improvements to make the dashboard engaging
and intuitive.
8. Frontend Technologies – Developed using Next.js, React, and javascript to ensure
performance and scalability. 
Nice-to-Haves (Enhancements for Better Usability & Insights)
1. Customisable Data Views – Ability for users to modify chart types and data filters
dynamically.
2. Drill-Down Functionality – Clicking on graphs to view deeper insights into specific user
activities or anomalies.
3. Anomaly Detection Alerts – Automated flagging of significant spikes or deviations in user
activity patterns.
4. Export Functionality – Allowing clients to export reports or graphs as images/PDFs for
documentation.
5. Localised Storage – The ability to save user preferences (e.g., selected date ranges, graph
types) locally for convenience.
Optional Outcomes (Future Features & Long-Term Integration)
1. Multi-File Data Merging – Ability to merge multiple CSV uploads into a consolidated dataset
for long-term analysis.
2. User Segmentation Filters – Allow filtering by user roles, departments, or specific behavioural
categories.
3. Predictive Analysis with Machine Learning – Advanced models to forecast potential risks
based on historical data trends.
4. Integration with ShadowSight SaaS – Connecting the dashboard to ShadowSight’s platform
for real-time data syncing (future phase).
5. Mobile-Friendly Design – Optimizing the dashboard for use on tablets and mobile devices. By
focusing on the must-haves first, this project will deliver a functional, visually engaging, and
machine learning-driven risk analysis dashboard while allowing room for future enhancements.